<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
I've chosen to play a Sorcerer.  I know that there aren't many of them.  I know that automatically means they are not widely considered to be uber.  If I wanted to do or be what everyone else was doing and being I wouldn't have chosen this class.<P>I want to enjoy my gaming experience.  I am, by and large, a role-player.  My sorceress has a rich history and a respected place in her guild.  While I don't sweat deaths or experience loss, (I often /release immediately, even though a rezzer "might" happen by).  I do have a hint of gamer in me.  So, I really like and enjoy brushing up on strategy and tactics.  I love perfecting the art of using the tools at my disposal.<P>So, I come to this forum assuming I would find such advice on strategy and tactics.  I could not have been more wrong.  This forum should be renamed "Why you should not play a Sorcerer".  Sorry, I've already made my decision.  <P>Is there any place where sorcerers go to discuss how to play the game AS IT IS, rather than complain about how it "should" be?
</FONT>
