Recently there's been a good amount of complaining, that's true.  But there's also been a good amount of strategy discussed.<P>I think a lot of sorcerors here have been with the class from fairly early -- I know that I have been, from day one.  It's interesting, as you look back at the threads from early on (say October/November), they're probably 90% strategy and advice, 10% other stuff including rants.<P>As people have stuck with the class, though, some of the persistent issues have begun to consume the other aspects of this board, as frustration has set in.  The frequent and long-time posters that have been here a while have already discussed and posted so much strategy that they may tend to complain more about their frustrations than to analyze a class which they already understand fairly well.  Thus, today, especially with regard to the to the long-time sorcerors here, it's probably 80% complaints and discussion of needed and recent changes, and 20% strategy and other stuff.<P>But -- in terms of overall knowledge of the class, you simply won't find a place to get your questions more completely and fully answered.  Moreover, if you look back over the months at the strategy posts, you'll probably already find your questions addressed in this forum.<P>So, even if you're the type of person who is inclined to be content with the class as it now exists, and unconcerned with your relative "power" but rather more concerned with the roleplaying experience, you've got a palce here.  Just understand that you're entering a board that is constantly evolving, with many devout sorcerors who DO care about their relative "power" and the evolution of a class that is still (and always will be) wonderful, yet in need of tweaks.<P>Should there be less negativity?  Yes, probably.  But can you still come here to get quick, accurate, and courteous answers to your sorceror issues?  Yes, definitely.<P>--------------------<P>--Kestrel Trebor, Sorceror<BR>The Sacred Brotherhood<BR>"Honor, loyalty, and above all, brotherhood!"<BR>Albion, Percival Server
